I risked a full ride and a stable career by leaving medical school to start entrepreneurship...⁣

I risked tried and true 7 figure a year bizs to go build something bigger in the social media world...⁣

And because of all those risks...I get to live this life today.⁣
⁣
Many of you have the chance to take the same risks and some of you will but some of you won't.⁣
⁣
But make sure as you make your choice...don't worry so much about what could go wrong but instead wonder what it would be like if it all goes exactly how you planned!⁣
⁣
Take more risks. Your future self will thank you one day!

In my mission to keep dropping free game and help people that could really use this info: this week dropped some basics on credit repair. Yes this topic is much more complex; we do 8 figures a year in this space! But let's make sure we educate everyone in these important topics! Info like this can really change someone's life!!

Many people think credit repair is illegal but this is not true. However, there are companies that are doing shady things that you must avoid.

You are allowed by law to validate the accuracy of your credit report and there are actually many protections that make sure there are not inaccurate items on your credit file.

Additionally, if items cannot be proven to be valid then they must consequently be removed from your credit report as well. 

Although you have rights as a consumer...there are companies that operate with shady tactics that could lead you into hot water.

If you are looking to get your credit fixed make sure you work with someone with a proven track record and most importantly ask what their process is.

Make sure they are not filing inaccurate claims on your behalf and filing legal documents or falsifying police reports.

Additionally, any good credit repair company will also have a through terms of service and legal contract. 

There are states that forbid credit repair such as Georgia so make sure the company you work with is in line with any state policies as well. 

For many this may be basic info but let's make sure we spread knowledge to those that need to hear this as well!

It took me a long time to realize this. And for the longest time I thought people who had all these "amazing" things must focus on getting them 24/7 and they must work so hard just to be able to buy them but the truth is it's only the unsuccessful people who fixate on these things and think having them will make them a better person. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sure the cool stuff is cool but really successful people, the people who have all this stuff in immense abundance and can buy it hundreds of times over, could care less about this shit. And once you start realizing this you start realizing that we've been brainwashed to always focus our precious energy on the wrong things and that's what really stops us from getting ahead.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sure the watches, the cars, the houses are all cool but what really excites someone that's truly successful is mastery, dominating an industry, being renowned in your field, the respect of other subject matter experts, teaching others and uplifting the next generation, being so great at something that you can make money over and over again without having to rely on anyone. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Study the greats and any high performers for that matter and you will quickly realize that they have an immense drive to better themselves and improve their skill sets, their knowledge base, their weaknesses, and everything in between.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So what I'm trying to get at is that if you really want these things you are going to need to put your energy, attention, money, and focus into making yourself the person who deserves all this stuff by focusing on the right things such as knowledge, mentors, courses, coaches, and just being a little bit better each and every day. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And the sooner you realize this the sooner you will actually start achieving the financial results, business results, and life results that you want not to mention all the cool watches and cars you could ever want to buy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So as you go on your journey to success and if you find yourself wanting the flashy stuff that's okay. Just make sure you focus on the real things that will get you there and you work on those things every single day. ⁣⁣

⁣
⁣
The fastest way to become a millionaire is to identify the habits that millionaires have have and start adopting them for yourself.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-Most millionaires became millionaires by having a contrarian mindset. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
By not following the crowd and doing what everyone else is doing. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And this makes sense because if you believe in efficient markets...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
the idea that as a market or industry becomes saturated and hyper competitive the edge anyone person has disappears...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
this naturally means you must get involved in industries that few people are in and are blue oceans.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-The second big concept you must focus on is catching trends. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Getting in early on Bitcoin, or e-commerce, or social media could have made you millions even if you weren’t great at it!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s impossible to get into every single trend but like Warren Buffet says you don’t need to hit every single home run you just need to make sure you don’t miss them all. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Start getting educated and aware of what’s happening in the world and start studying what people hate the most. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve found that the things people hate the most end up having the biggest up side when the narrative changes. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Also, start studying what the young generations are thinking and focused on. They drive the trends!!!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-Lastly, surround yourself with other millionaires or people who want to become millionaires.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The fastest way to adopt their habits and think like them is to spend time with them. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Make sure you never sleep on investing in events, mentors, and networking. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Aside from eduction...networking will offer you the second biggest ROI in your entrepreneur journey! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Lastly, have patience. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The fastest way for you may still take 2 years...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve been at this entrepreneur game for so many years now...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
don’t get anxious or quit if it takes longer than you think! Remember what you are working for and never give up on your family or yourself! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Stay positive, keep working, keep learning, and I promise your time will come!

Got to spend a few days in LA handling some biz and also ran up a bunch of money in the financial markets. Life is good when you can live the life you want to live, be around the people you want to be around, and make an impact in the world and have fun while doing it.

I remember riding in Honda civics back in the day and still having the same joy I have for life right now. If you are struggling and you aren't there yet here are my 5 top tips to stay focused and keep working until you get there. 

1. Stay patient. Remember that your goals are big and that's why they may be taking some time. Never get discouraged. Remember everyone started from zero stay focused and never quit and eventually you will get there. 

2. Look for the right people. People are the most important thing and will determine what level of success you have. Even if you have to pay to be around the right people do it! 

3. Always keep learning. One thing I can say is that what I know now is on a entirely different level cognitively then me just a year ago. Always keep learning. The day you stop learning so the day you strip growing. 

4. If you can have fun with what you do then do it. Work is hard. Making money is hard. Success is hard. But if you can get into fields that you enjoy it'll be a lot easier to go the mile and not quit. 

5. You can't catch all investments but you can catch a few. Even Warren Buffet missed Google and Amazon and he's considered the greatest investor of all time. The truth is you only need to catch a few home runs to get rich. There will be many life changing opportunities and you will miss MOST of them. The key is to not miss all of them!

As soon as you start doing well, people will begin hoping for you to stop 😯😤

The TRUTH is people are really out here holding their breath waiting for you to FAIL. 

So you might as well make sure they SUFFOCATE and keep waiting forever. 

And if you wanna make a lot of money or win big in life you must be able to outwork the people who want to see you lose. 

You see, I might not always be the smartest or most skilled in what I do but I know for damn sure I will never quit before my haters do.

When I started leveraging my credit to make money, people told me I could never turn that into a full time income...yet I went and made millions with MS and arbitrage. 🥳

When people told me dropping out of med school was a bad idea to support my family they didn't expect me to actually succeed and retire my entire family before they even graduated. 😱😎

When people told me it was too hard to build a brand on social media because I didn't have industry connections, I still made it happen anyways building over 2 million followers and getting verified ✔️ 

When people said I couldn't teach others what I knew and I just had gotten lucky...I created hundreds of success stories and built thousands of people's credit and finances. Literally making the whole credit industry as popular as it is today amongst the younger crowd anyways. 👑💸💎💰

When people said don't teach others the real game because they will be your competition...I looked at the big picture and made hundreds of bosses. Most likely whoever you see on social media talking about credit I taught them or I taught their mentor 😂😂😂

At the end of the day...a lot of people have a lot to say...but just make sure your actions and hard work always gets the last laugh. Yes people are waiting for you to fail...but to me that's just motivation to make sure I make them quit before I do 🤷🏻‍♂️😤💥💸✔️

Life is Black and White…🖤☑️

Most people just make it more complicated that it really is by looking for their answers in the Grey areas 🤦🏻‍♂️

We as humans try to make excuses, defer the blame, and complain instead of just doing the work. 😅

And despite seeing others win and live the dream life that we want, we tell ourselves its impossible for us or they they must have lied or cheated to get what they have. 😤

But the TRUTH is whatever you have in life, you had to work hard for and you actually deserved it. 

And whatever you don’t have you simply didn’t. Atleast NOT hard enough as judged by the marketplace. 💥

And many people will say that's not true and make excuses about how some people get handed their wealth. 

But where did their family get it from? 

Wealth didn't come from nothing. Someone somewhere had to do the work and did it and that's why their family has it like that today...so why not you!? 🙏🏻💸

And that’s a TRUTH most people don’t want to accept. The fact will always be that the marketplace rewards merit accordingly.

Sometimes not right away. Sometimes it can take time. But the marketplace always rewards those who put value into the world. 

And so if you are reading this and don’t have what you want and aren’t living the life you want to live…or maybe you are but know you could do a lot better…

Understand that you can change and your life can change. But you must put away all the bullshit excuses you tell yourself and stop playing in the grey areas of life…and commit to the black and white. 

Realize that you are either going to do it or you're not. And each time things get tough and you begin to get in your head or overthink or make excuses ask yourself am I getting closer to my goals or am I not? 

And any action that doesn't get you closer cut it out completely 😤

Do the Work...get the Result. That's the formula. And if you're reading this even if times get tough or things get hard just keep going! Your time is about to come! 🙏🏻

If they're not on your TIME…TIME to let them go 😱💥

Listen carefully...

My 1st semester at Cornell I got 2 C’s in Biology & Chemistry…& if you don’t know you might as well call it quits as a premed if this happens. 

I got a perfect ACT, crushed the hardest classes, got into an Ivy League, and I had made my disabled immigrant parents prouder than ever in their entire life. 

And I remember calling my Dad and telling him I didn’t do well…

Him asking me what grade I got...

And for the 1st time in my life, me always telling my Dad every thing even wrong I had done, hesitating and telling my best friend, my father, I can’t tell you.

And I remember my Dad going ballistic.

And that semester, I realized I was on a different TIME than anyone else. 

Other kids, maybe their parents were Senators, or worked at Goldman Sachs, or had family money, or were legacies at the med or law school…and were just set…BUT I wasn’t…

I grew up poor. I had no fall back. I had no trust fund. Daddy didn’t have a company I could work at. We had no connections. It was do or die. It was make it now or be nothing and go back to welfare and food stamps.

And I realized quickly that while the other kids could have study sessions and waste 4-6 hours gossiping…I couldn’t. 

While they could go to parties or dates, I couldn’t. 

And when my roommate watched Boondocks Saints 16 hrs/day…it meant I had to go to the library & leave my own room the entire day. 

And guess what. The next 3 years I got 26 A+s, TA'd 3 classes, published research in a science journal, had 1000 volunteer hours, & the highest MCAT in my class. 

And it all happened bc I cut off people that weren't on my TIME.

And people on my TIME…one is at Harvard Biz School, another is making 4 mill a year at NYC’s most prestigious M&A law firm, another is a professor at Stanford, and me I’ve built multiple 7 & 8 fig bizs & we are all STILL in our 20s!

So listen, if you're really serious about making it, understand…if they're not on your TIME…TIME to let them go and get w/ people who are. 

So if you want to roll with the right crew & Dominate your biz DM Me "TIME" 🤝💥

You have to be willing to look stupid in front of a few if you want to be great in front of many...especially if that many is millions 🙏🏻

I've gotten my share of congrats this week but understand it came after years of criticism. 

You see when I started out I had absolutely zero money, zero followers, zero branding...

And yes I was an entrepreneur but I didn't even own any bizs...

And even when I pitched people I had no idea what I was even saying 😂😭

And truth be told, I really looked stupid to a lot of people. 

I had no bizs. I made no money. I wasn't a leader. I didn't influence people and I had no impact. Yet I really wanted to!

And for many years, I worked hard but I really did look stupid trying to change my life. 

I don't even blame my closest friends and family for thinking how stupid I looked.

They thought they were helping me by criticizing me for working so hard yet making no progress.

They thought they were gonna save me by pushing me to quit volatile entrepreneurship to go get a real job. 

But they didn't know I was cut out for this sh*t. 

You see, I realized a long time ago that you can either make people around you happy or you could make yourself happy but you can't do both at the same time. 

So as you go on this path of chasing your dreams realize that looking stupid, being criticized, and pissing people off is part of the game. But just don't let it discourage you. 

Bc one day you will impact millions bc you didn't give up. And even the people you alienated or thought you looked so stupid they will all try to come back in your life anyways to say sorry...and also to ask for money 😂🤣😭 just make sure to tell them it's too risky of a move like they told you 😂

But anyways if you made it this far...just understand criticism is part of the game. So if your path gets hard just remember it's supposed to be and keep going until your impact turns into millions of people.  🙏🏻💥✊🏻

Trust me if a broke kid from the trailer park in nowhere Alabama with disabled immigrant parents could do it...you can to. God is the Greatest.
